    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing it with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly slice your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Slice your<strong> potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into discs</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>sliced ginger </strong>and <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and cook for 2-3 mins or until starting to soften</p><p>Once starting to soften, add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, reduce the heat to medium and add your <strong>tamarind paste</strong> and your <strong>soy sauce</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>chopped carrot</strong>, <strong>sliced potato </strong>and <strong>cauliflower florets </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with 700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[1L]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-22 min or until the veg and potato is softened \u2013 this is your <strong>soup base</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>to a small heatproof bowl</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>and cook for 20-30 secs or until the butter is melted</p><p>Once the butter is melted, add your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and give a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the soup base is ready, remove the pot from the heat and add your <strong>cultured coconut</strong>,<strong> </strong>a generous squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and blitz with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> until smooth</p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut & cauliflower soup</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a toaster for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-fragrant-coconut-and-cauliflower-soup-with-chilli-butter/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> coconut & cauliflower soup </strong>and top with your <strong>pine kernel & seed mix</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>chilli butter </strong>and garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>warmed naan[s] </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
